# Single place for your OpenRouter key (repo root, same folder as README.md).
#
# Easiest on Windows: double-click START-CLAW.bat. It opens a terminal,
# asks for a key if missing/invalid/no-response, saves `.env`, validates
# OpenRouter with a live authenticated request, then launches Claw.
#
# Manual path:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env` in the repo root.
#   2. Replace YOUR_OPENROUTER_KEY_HERE with your real OpenRouter API key once.
#   3. Run:  START-CLAW.bat
#
# `.env` is gitignored so your key is not pushed by mistake.
#
# After you set a real key, verify it in the terminal (live OpenRouter check):
#   Double-click CHECK-KEY.bat (shows the full command, then runs it), or
#   OPEN-KEY-CHECK-WINDOW.bat (same in a new window), or:
#   powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\validate-openrouter.ps1
# Change the key from the CLI (hidden paste) without Notepad:
#   Double-click UPDATE-KEY.bat   or   .\set-openrouter-key.ps1
# `claw doctor` only checks that variables exist locally; it does not call OpenRouter.
# START-CLAW.bat performs the live validation before running doctor
# (GET /v1/auth/key; not GET /v1/credits, which needs a management key).
# The Windows helper batch files temporarily clear inherited OPENAI_API_KEY and
# OPENAI_BASE_URL values so this .env file is the validation source of truth.

OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
OPENAI_API_KEY=YOUR_OPENROUTER_KEY_HERE
